    writer {
      name: "Oscar Vazquez"
    }
    rating: "Decent"
    comments: "The dialogue is very meta and kinda pretencious at times, but besides that, it feels like any other documentary; the humor is pretty good, with them making a lot of jokes that push the rating limit; the symbolism is decent as the movie is a metaphor on how pieces come togheter to make bigger concepts and aspects of life, why they decided to make this movie with legos; they try to have this political message towards the end of the movie, but there is barely any time life and they kinda just brush over it, so it felt like they had it just to have it without presenting any nuance; the foreshadowing is alright, but kinda predictable if you know Pharrell's life"
  }
